contentrichtext.text: {{Orphan|date=February 2009}} '''Oslo Baseballklubb''' ('''Oslo Pretenders''') has been the leading [[baseball]] team in [[Norway]] since 1991, winning fifteen National Championships. In addition the Pretenders have won twelve League Titles. The team has also participated in the [[European Cup (baseball)|European Cup]] every year since 2001. The philosophy of the team is to maintain and promote the character of the individual to create a dynamic team of different mentalities. The team also works with children aged 8 to 14. No woman's team currently exists as part of the club, but women are welcome to participate on either team. It is a non-profit organization. ==External links== *[http://www.oslopretenders.com oslopretenders.com] *[http://www.oslopretenders.com/content/Vedtekter.doc By-laws of the Oslo Pretenders Baseball Club] (.doc, in Norwegian) [[Category:Baseball teams]] [[Category:Sports teams in Norway]] {{Norway-sport-team-stub}} {{Europe-baseball-team-stub}}
